Operations.Message:
-------------------------------------
  FOREST BRUSH
-------------------------------------
This brush gives you the ability to create forests.

-------------------------------------
 How to use
-------------------------------------

Right Click: Edits the blocks to create a forest floor.

Left Click: Adds decorations to the forest floor (Boulders, Trees, Foliage). Use the Decoration Types dropdown to select the type of decoration. If using Foliage, use the inputs with the word "Foliage" to control these settings.

-------------------------------------
 Customize the brush
-------------------------------------

This brush has customizable settings so you can create your paths how you want them. Below are each setting and what they do:

Decoration Types = The decorations offered by the brush. Here are the current settings:

          Boulders: Places down boulder prefabs

          Trees: Places down tree prefabs (use "Tree Types" dropdown to select what trees)

          Foliage: Places down plants and other materials on top of the forest floor

Tree Types = Dropdown of available trees to place as decorations.

Foliage Blocks = The materials that make up the plants that will be placed on top of the forest floor.

Foliage Density = How dense the Foliage Blocks will be.

Primary Blocks = The primary materials to make up the forest floor.

Primary Density = How dense the Primary Blocks will be.

Patch Blocks = The materials to make up patches within the Primary Blocks.

Patch Density = How dense the Patch Blocks will be.

Secondary Blocks = The secondary materials to make up the forest floor. This will be the outline around the forest floor.

Secondary Density = How dense the Secondary Blocks will be.

Forest Brush Documentation:

The comment to the left of this comment block is the documentation that will be sent in the chat when the player first tries to use the brush. The documentation in this comment block will detail about the brush itself in the node editor.

The prefab list assets used in this brush were auto generated via a script. It lists all the folders in a given root folder you specify. If any folders or prefabs in these folders are changed, it will effect this brush.
